%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Eligible Home Health Care services include an intermittent skilled nursing care, physical therapy, occupational therapy, speech-language therapy.  Maximum Reasonable Guidelines apply to Out of Network Expenses
Name: Home Health Care Eligible Services

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Following a Hospital stay. Limited  30 calendar days from the discharge date of the Member's Inpatient Hospital stay, after the ISA is met, eligible expenses are 100% shared up to the Maximum Limit per Incident
Name: Home Health Care

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Eligible Expenses are shared after ISA is met. The PCP or Urgent Care Visit fee may apply, for general testing, performed in a PCP/ Urgent Care Facility. Diagnostics such as MRI, Cat/Pet Scans, Pathology labs are not included in Visit fee. ISA applies.
Name: Laboratory Services, Diagnostic and X-rays

%vlocity_namespace%__AttributeDisplayNam: Outpatient Therapy: Physical, Occupational, and Speech Therapy Limits
%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Up to 10 Combined Visits per incident.  Number of Visits will be reduced by any Physical, Occupational and/or Speech Therapy received under Home Health Care Services. Maximum Reasonable Guidelines apply to Out of Network Expenses.
Name: Outpatient Therapy: Physical, Occupational, and Speech Therapy Limits

%vlocity_namespace%__AttributeDisplayNam: Outpatient Therapy: Physical, Occupational, and Speech Therapy
%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: For conditions related to an eligible diagnosis, OT, PT ST, performed by a licensed therapist expenses are Eligible for sharing after a $20 Visit Fee, per visit up to the Maximum Limit Per Incident.
Name: Outpatient Therapy: Physical, Occupational, and Speech Therapy

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Limited to 2 visits and up to a maximum $500 sharing per Program Year. Shoes, socks, insoles, materials, and equipment are Not Eligible for Sharing.
Name: Podiatry Limits

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Routine podiatry services, provided by a doctor of podiatric medicine, are eligible for sharing after the Member’s ISA is met.
Name: Podiatry

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Preventive Services and one Wellness Visit : Eligible Expenses 100% Shared up to $1,000 Maximum per program year
Name: Preventive Services and Wellness Visit

%vlocity_namespace%__AttributeDisplayNam: Primary Care Physician Visit Fee and Frequency
%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: $20 Visit Fee; limit 4 visits per Member per Program Year. Maximum Reasonable Guidelines apply to Out of Network expenses
Name: Primary Care Physician Visit Fee and Frequency

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Non-Surgical Services for the diagnosis, treatment, management or prevention of an illness or injury. Diagnostic imaging such as MRI, Cat Scans, Pet Scans and pathology labs are not included in the Visit Fee and the ISA will separately apply.
Name: Primary Care Physician Visit

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: Following the period after the  ISA is met, up to the Maximum Limit Per Incident. Life Threatening or Life Altering emergencies are immediately eligible for sharing. Maximum Reasonable Guidelines apply to Out of Network expenses.
Name: Surgery

%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: For the diagnosis, treatment, management of an eligible illness or injury serious enough that a member would seek care right away, but not so severe as to require Hospital emergency department care.
Name: Urgent Care

%vlocity_namespace%__AttributeDisplayNam: Urgent Case Visit Fee and Frequency
%vlocity_namespace%__Value__c: $20 Visit Fee; limit 1 visit per Member per Program Year. Maximum Reasonable Guidelines apply to Out of Network expenses.
Name: Urgent Case Visit Fee and Frequency
